      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WONDER I DO (1) could manage only seventh after making contact in the run last time in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park, finishing 7 lengths from the winner (30.24). Rates on top in this line up. GUS AND DODO (2) recorded a 2.5 lengths win (19.96) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Has already won three times from this draw. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. JAYLA MAGIC (7) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Saint Rico (24.92) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Comes through a solid form race last start. Will give a great sight again. BIG TED (6) hit the frame here last start so don't underestimate.",
